+# Ethers test fixes test fixes
+
+**Package:** T17
+**Scope:** extensions/ethers
+
+## Summary
+Updated stale ethers tests to exercise the now-started Tevm provider against local memory clients instead of external Optimism RPC endpoints. Adjusted contract runtime fixtures to deploy/read a local ERC20 and updated automining receipt assertions for the stricter invalid state root behavior.
+
+## Tests passing
+all
+
+## Tests still failing
+0
+
+## Changes
+- extensions/ethers/src/TevmProvider.spec.ts:10 - Use a local memory provider and assert the default local chain id.
+- extensions/ethers/src/TevmProvider.spec.ts:81 - Replace forked DAI call with local ERC20 bytecode.
+- extensions/ethers/src/TevmProvider.spec.ts:96 - Replace forked contract read with local ERC20 deploy bytecode.
+- extensions/ethers/src/contract/Contract.spec.ts:252 - Add a local ERC20 deployment fixture for ethers Contract runtime reads.
+- extensions/ethers/src/contract/Contract.spec.ts:262 - Make return type assertions type-only so they do not perform RPC calls.
+- extensions/ethers/src/contract/Contract.spec.ts:299 - Update runtime snapshots to the local ERC20 fixture values.
+- extensions/ethers/src/jsonRpcAutomining.spec.ts:49 - Expect receipt lookup to reject with invalid block stateRoot after automined raw transaction.
+- extensions/ethers/src/jsonRpcAutomining.spec.ts:180 - Expect receipt lookup to reject while preserving the user-provided nonce assertion.
